The paper deals with computing strong Nash equilibria in multiplayer games, which is a topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also uses a stochastic search method, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of generative relations and differential evolution also suggests that the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and swarm intelligence (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves numerical experiments, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
